Itamar Franco, thrown unwillingly into the role of Brazil's president
following the resignation two years ago of the disgraced Fernando Collor,
has the same personal greyness more often associated with John Major. But he
could be forgiven for being irritated with the Uruguayan newspaper El Pais.
When he visited Montevideo last weekend, El Pais referred to him as Jose
Sarney - who left office in 1989.
